tables.table_schema: CREATE TABLE ProteinInteractionData (   interaction_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,   protein_one_id INT NOT NULL,   protein_two_id INT NOT NULL,   interaction_score FLOAT NOT NULL,   interaction_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL );

CREATE TABLE protein_interactions (
  interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  protein_id_1 INT NOT NULL,
  protein_id_2 INT NOT NULL,
  interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
  interaction_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE Interactions(
    interaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protein_id_1 INT NOT NULL,
    protein_id_2 INT NOT NULL,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    interaction_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE protein_interactions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    protein1_id INT,
    protein2_id INT,
    interaction_type VARCHAR(50),
    interaction_strength FLOAT
);
CREATE TABLE Protein(id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), function VARCHAR(255), sequence TEXT)
CREATE TABLE Interaction(id INT PRIMARY KEY, protein1_id INT, protein2_id INT, interaction_type VARCHAR(50), date DATE)
CREATE TABLE Complex(id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(255), description TEXT, predicted BOOLEAN)
CREATE TABLE ComplexProteins(id INT PRIMARY KEY, complex_id INT, protein_id INT)
CREATE TABLE Experiment(id INT PRIMARY KEY, complex_id INT, date DATE, result TEXT)
